```go
// SaveMigrationHistory saves the entire migration history
func (s *Storage) SaveMigrationHistory(ctx *log.Context, history MigrationHistory) error {
	const functionName = "data_migration.Storage.SaveMigrationHistory"

	// Save history to Consul
	if err := s.consulClient.PutKey(MigrationHistoryKey, history); err != nil {
		return errors.Wrap(err, functionName)
	}

	return nil
}
```

This optimization:

1. Loads the migration history from Consul only once at the beginning
2. Uses the map for O(1) lookups to check if a migration has been executed
3. Updates the local copy of executed migrations when a new migration is successful
4. Only saves back to Consul once at the end if any migrations were executed

This will be much more efficient, especially when you have many migrations and most of them have already been executed.


